HEADWORD: Porcate
<hw>Por"cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>porca</ets>
a ridge between two furrows.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having
grooves or furrows broader than the intervening ridges;
furrowed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

